    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>CSS custom properties</strong> (<code>--*</code>, <code>@property</code>)</td>
      <td>Mint any <code>--x</code> with zero registration; <code>@property</code> / <code>CSS.registerProperty()</code> optionally adds a type contract</td>
      <td><strong>The <code>--</code> marker</strong> — "&lt;dashed-ident&gt; will never be defined in CSS"; a structural guaranteed-collision-free space. Finer prefixes (<code>--tw-</code>, <code>--app-</code>) are convention only</td>
      <td><strong>Both</strong> — <code>@property</code> declarative (CSS) or <code>CSS.registerProperty()</code> runtime (JS wins on tie); values resolved at runtime by the cascade</td>
    </tr>
